item.title: Easy but complicated
item.dc:creator: @dddylan98 dddylan98
item.description:
@dddylan98 wrote:

Ok, go into your program files, and check the java folder and find a jdk. It should say something like “jdk1.6.0_29”. Go into your run.bat, right click, and edit it. Where you see the C:/Programs/java/jdk1.6.0_xx Change the XX to your jdk version. Mine is JDK 6 update 29.
